===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[heorte]]'', from {{Ger.}} ''*xirtan'', from Indo-European ''*k̑erd-''.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[hart#Dutch|hart]]'', German ''[[Herz]]'', Swedish ''[[hjärta]]''.  The Indo-European root is also the source of Greek ''[[καρδία]]'', Latin ''[[cor]]'', Welsh ''[[craidd]]'', Russian ''[[сердце]]'', Lithuanian ''[[širdis]]''.

